node.title: New community COVID case detected on Brisbane's bayside, contact tracing locations named
node.alt: Dr Peter Aitken speaks at a media conference in Brisbane.
node.description: A new community case is confirmed in Queensland, with aÂ public health alert issued for contact tracing locations in Capalaba, in the city of Redland, on Brisbane's bayside.
node.content:
["A new community case has been confirmed in Queensland, with a\u00a0public health alert issued for contact tracing locations in Capalaba, in the city of Redland, on Brisbane's bayside.", "Contact tracing and investigation is underway, with more details to be released once available tomorrow.", "Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk said it was a reminder for Queenslanders to regularly check official websites.", "\"This is a timely reminder for all Queenslanders to regularly monitor the list of exposure venues on the Queensland Health website and follow the public health advice, as there may be more locations,\" the Premier said in a Facebook post.", "The list includes a close contact site at Sit at Siam Thai Restaurant on Old Cleveland Road, Capalaba.", "As always, ensure you check\u00a0the health advice in the table below (click \"More\" if you are on a mobile device) for what to do if you have visited any of the sites rated as close contact, casual contact\u00a0or low-risk contact.", "The Queensland Health contact tracing sites list is regularly updated as new information comes to hand.", "
Gold Coast case not linked to previous cases
", "", "
The recent positive COVID case visited Robina Town Centre sales last Friday.(ABC News: Steve Keen)
", "Earlier, genomic tests revealed the latest COVID-19 case detected on the Gold Coast is not linked to any recent local cases there.", "Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken said he believed\u00a0it had\u00a0been transmitted through an unknown interstate \"incursion\".", "There were two cases detected today in home quarantine and four in hotel quarantine.", "Dr Aitken said genomic sequencing on\u00a0the man who tested positive on the Gold Coast on Wednesday\u00a0has today linked the case to previous outbreaks in New South Wales.", "\"We don't know how he got it at this stage,\" Dr Aitken said.", "\"The most likely cause is there has been an incursion somewhere from New South Wales.", "\"We need to make sure that no-one else on the Gold Coast has been exposed and may have COVID there.\"", "Health Minister Yvette D'Ath encouraged people on the Gold Coast to get tested and vaccinated.", "\"[The recent case]\u00a0means someone has been on the Gold Coast and may still be on there, or elsewhere in Queensland, who is positive and haven't been identified as yet,\" she said.", "She said 2,154 people were tested for the virus in the region in the past 24 hours.", "\"So this reinforces the importance of everyone coming forward if you've got any symptoms, no matter how mild, to get tested, and importantly, getting those vaccination rates up.\"", "Ms D'Ath said there would be no new border restrictions placed on South Australia despite an outbreak there, but she said authorities were \"closely\" monitoring the situation.", "", "
Outbreak: How Australia lost control of the Delta variant
